1. Product Requirements Document (PRD)
1.1 Project Overview
Drivera is a B2B fleet rental web platform that connects businesses needing bulk vehicle rentals with verified fleet suppliers. The platform simplifies the traditionally fragmented vehicle rental market by offering centralized search, bulk booking, supplier verification, and fleet management in a single interface.
1.2 Problem Statement
Businesses requiring bulk vehicle rentals — logistics firms, event companies, corporate travel departments — face three core friction points:
▸	No single platform for bulk B2B fleet searches across multiple suppliers
▸	No standardized supplier verification or trust mechanism
▸	Manual booking processes lacking real-time availability and centralized billing
1.3 Objectives
▸	Allow businesses (renters) to search, compare, and book fleets in bulk
▸	Allow suppliers to list fleets, manage availability, and receive bookings
▸	Implement a supplier verification layer ('Verified Supplier' badge)
▸	Provide a real-time map-based supplier discovery interface
▸	Support fleet tracking dashboard post-booking
1.4 Target Users
Primary — Renters
▸	Corporate travel and logistics managers
▸	Event management companies
▸	SMEs requiring temporary fleet expansion
Secondary — Suppliers
▸	Fleet owners with 10+ vehicles
▸	Vehicle rental agencies offering B2B contracts
1.5 Functional Requirements
1.5.1 Landing Page / Home
▸	Hero section: 'Fleet Rentals, Simplified for Business' with CTA buttons (Book a Fleet, For Suppliers)
▸	How it Works: Search & Select → Book in Bulk → Manage & Track
▸	Why Drivera: Bulk Booking, Centralized Billing, Real-time Tracking, Verified Suppliers
1.5.2 User (Renter) Module
▸	Register/Login with email
▸	Search suppliers by: location, vehicle type, fleet size, date range
▸	Map view with supplier pins and popup cards (distance, rating, price/day, availability)
▸	List view with supplier cards (verified badge, fleet count, rating, pricing)
▸	Bulk booking with fleet size selection and date picker
▸	Booking confirmation and history dashboard
1.5.3 Supplier Module
▸	Register as supplier with company details
▸	List fleet inventory: vehicle type, count, price/day, location
▸	View and manage incoming booking requests
▸	Verification application (admin-approved 'Verified Supplier' badge)
1.5.4 Admin Module
▸	Approve/reject supplier verification requests
▸	View platform-wide booking and revenue metrics
▸	Manage users and suppliers
1.6 Non-Functional Requirements
▸	Response time < 2 seconds for search queries
▸	Mobile-responsive layout across all pages
▸	SQL injection prevention via parameterized queries (Flask-MySQL)
▸	Password hashing with bcrypt
▸	SDLC documentation: SRS, ER Diagram, Normalized Schema, Test Cases
1.7 Out of Scope (for this submission)
▸	Payment gateway integration
▸	Real-time GPS vehicle tracking
▸	Native mobile app
 
2. Technology Stack
2.1 Stack Overview

Layer	Technology	Rationale
Frontend	HTML5 + CSS3 + Vanilla JS	No framework overhead; full control; matches Drivera design system
Backend	Python 3.11 + Flask 3.x	Lightweight, fast to scaffold, strong MySQL ecosystem
Database	MySQL 8.x	Matches DBMS practical schema; familiar SQL, SPPU-compliant
ORM / DB	Flask-MySQLdb / mysql-connector-python	Direct query control; no abstraction hiding SQL
Auth	Flask-Login + bcrypt	Session management + secure password hashing
Maps	Google Maps JS Embed API (free tier)	Supplier location pins matching Drivera booking screen
Deployment	Render (free web service)	Free, GitHub-connected, persistent DB via PlanetScale or Railway
IDE	Google Antigravity	Agent-first scaffolding, terminal + browser automation
Version Control	Git + GitHub	Required for Render deployment pipeline

